# ERROR HANDLING TESTS
# ============================================

### Missing Query (Should Error)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/ai/query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "65a123abc456"
}

###

### Missing User ID (Should Error)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/ai/query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "Show me students"
}

###

### Invalid Endpoint (Should Error)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/ai/query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "test",
  "userId": "invalid_id"
}

# ============================================
# NOTES
# ============================================

# Replace the IDs with actual IDs from your database:
# - 65a123abc456 = Replace with actual teacher ID
# - 65a456def789 = Replace with actual class ID
# - 65a789ghi012 = Replace with actual parent ID
# - 65a333xyz789 = Replace with actual student ID

# Test with REST Client Extension:
# 1. Install "REST Client" extension in VS Code
# 2. Open this file
# 3. Click "Send Request" above any request
# 4. View response in the new panel

